# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Vibe-Coder v3.0 — Environment Variables
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your API keys.
# ALL keys are optional — the system works with any combination.
# More keys = more capabilities.
#
# Usage: cp .env.example .env && nano .env
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ─── Layer 3: Supermemory (Long-term cross-session memory) ───────
# Get your key at: https://supermemory.ai
# Used by: All interfaces (MCP or CLI)
# Purpose: Persistent memory across sessions and projects (#1 on benchmarks)
SUPERMEMORY_API_KEY=sm_your_api_key_here

# ─── Layer 4: OpenViking (Codebase context memory) ───────────────
# Docs: https://www.openviking.ai/docs
# Used by: Claude Code, Cursor (MCP); others via CLI
# Purpose: Codebase context with L0/L1/L2 tiered loading (91% token reduction)

# VLM Provider (choose one: openai, volcengine, litellm)
OPENVIKING_VLM_PROVIDER=openai
OPENVIKING_VLM_MODEL=gpt-4o
OPENVIKING_VLM_API_KEY=sk-your_openai_key_here

# Embedding Provider
OPENVIKING_EMBEDDING_PROVIDER=openai
OPENVIKING_EMBEDDING_MODEL=text-embedding-3-large
OPENVIKING_EMBEDDING_API_KEY=sk-your_openai_key_here

# ─── MCP: Nano-Banana (Image generation via Gemini) ─────────────
# Get your key at: https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
# Used by: All interfaces
# Purpose: AI image generation for mockups, icons, design concepts
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here

# ─── MCP: MCP-Toolbox (Database access) ─────────────────────────
# Not needed if you don't use database features.
# Supports: PostgreSQL, MySQL, BigQuery, MongoDB, Redis, 20+ more
# Docs: https://github.com/googleapis/genai-toolbox
#
# Example for PostgreSQL:
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@localhost:5432/mydb
#
# Example for MySQL:
# DATABASE_URL=mysql://user:pass@localhost:3306/mydb

# ─── MCP: MarkItDown (File conversion) ──────────────────────────
# No API key needed — runs locally.
# Install: pip install markitdown
# Purpose: Convert PDF, DOCX, XLSX, images, audio → Markdown

# ─── MCP: Code-Review-Graph (AST code graph) ────────────────────
# No API key needed — runs locally with SQLite.
# Install: pip install code-review-graph
# Purpose: 8.2x token reduction via structural code analysis
#
# Optional: embeddings for semantic search
# CODE_REVIEW_GRAPH_EMBEDDING_PROVIDER=google  # or: local, minimax
# CODE_REVIEW_GRAPH_EMBEDDING_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here

# ─── MCP: Lightpanda (Fast browser) ─────────────────────────────
# No API key needed — runs locally.
# Install: curl -L -o lightpanda https://github.com/lightpanda-io/browser/releases/download/nightly/lightpanda-aarch64-macos && chmod a+x ./lightpanda
# Purpose: 9x faster browser for web tasks (NEVER use Chrome)

# ─── MCP: GitNexus (Codebase map) ───────────────────────────────
# No API key needed — runs via npx.
# Usage: npx -y gitnexus@latest mcp
# Purpose: Codebase structure analysis and mapping

# ─── MCP: Task Master (AI task management) ──────────────────────
# Uses your Claude/OpenAI API key for AI-powered task decomposition.
# Get key at: https://console.anthropic.com/
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your_anthropic_key_here

# Alternative: use OpenAI for Task Master
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your_openai_key_here

# ─── MCP: Claude-Flow (Agent teams — Claude Code only) ──────────
# Uses your Anthropic API key (same as above).
# Only works in Claude Code with CLAUDE_CODE_EXPERIMENTAL_AGENT_TEAMS=1

# ─── Optional: Claude Code Agent Teams ──────────────────────────
# Enables multi-agent coordination in Claude Code.
CLAUDE_CODE_EXPERIMENTAL_AGENT_TEAMS=1

# ─── Optional: cc-connect (Remote access from chat platforms) ────
# Only needed if you want AI agents accessible from Telegram/Slack/Discord.
# Docs: COMBINED/orchestration/core-cc-connect/
# TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=your_telegram_bot_token
# SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=xoxb-your-slack-bot-token
# DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=your_discord_bot_token

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SUMMARY — What needs API keys vs what runs locally:
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# RUNS LOCALLY (no keys needed):
#   ✅ code-review-graph  — SQLite AST graph (MANDATORY)
#   ✅ lightpanda          — Fast browser
#   ✅ gitnexus            — Codebase mapping
#   ✅ markitdown          — File conversion
#
# NEEDS API KEY:
#   🔑 supermemory         — Long-term memory
#   🔑 openviking          — Codebase context (needs LLM key)
#   🔑 nano-banana         — Image generation (Gemini key)
#   🔑 mcp-toolbox         — Database access (connection string)
#   🔑 task-master         — AI task management (Anthropic/OpenAI key)
#   🔑 claude-flow         — Agent teams (Anthropic key)
#
# OPTIONAL (for remote access):
#   🔑 cc-connect          — Telegram/Slack/Discord bots
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
